---
	import Layout from '@/layout/base-layout.astro';
	import Prose from '@/ui/prose.astro';
---
<Layout title="Prose Recipe Demo">
	<main class="container max-w-4xl mx-auto py-8 px-4">
		<Prose size="lg" lead>
			<h1>Prose Recipe Demonstration</h1>

			<p>
				This page demonstrates the comprehensive typography system built with
				our prose recipe. The first paragraph is styled as a lead paragraph with
				larger text and muted color to introduce the content effectively.
			</p>

			<h2>Typography Hierarchy</h2>

			<p>
				The prose recipe provides a complete typography scale that creates clear
				visual hierarchy and excellent readability. All elements are properly
				spaced and styled for optimal reading experience.
			</p>

			<h3>Lists and Structure</h3>

			<p>Here's an ordered list showing key features:</p>

			<ol>
				<li>
					<strong>Comprehensive element support</strong>- All HTML elements are
					styled
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Multiple size variants</strong>- From compact to extra large
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Color variants</strong>- Default, muted, and inverted themes
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Responsive design</strong>- Adapts to different screen sizes
				</li>
			</ol>

			<p>And here's an unordered list of typography best practices:</p>

			<ul>
				<li>Maintain consistent spacing between elements</li>
				<li>Use proper heading hierarchy (h1 → h2 → h3...)</li>
				<li>Keep line lengths readable (45-75 characters)</li>
				<li>Ensure sufficient color contrast</li>
			</ul>

			<h3>Code Examples</h3>

			<p>
				The recipe handles both inline code like
				<code>const example = true;</code>and code blocks with proper
				formatting:
			</p>

			<pre><code>import &#123; prose &#125; from '@styled-system/recipes';

const proseClasses = prose(&#123;
  size: 'lg',
  variant: 'default',
  lead: true
&#125;);

console.log('Prose recipe applied!');</code></pre>

			<h3>Blockquotes</h3>

			<blockquote>
				<p>
					"Typography is the craft of endowing human language with a durable
					visual form." — Robert Bringhurst, The Elements of Typographic Style
				</p>
			</blockquote>

			<p>
				Blockquotes are styled with subtle borders and background colors to make
				them stand out from regular content while maintaining readability.
			</p>

			<h2>Tables and Data</h2>

			<p>The prose recipe also handles tabular data with proper styling:</p>

			<table>
				<thead>
					<tr>
						<th>Size Variant</th>
						<th>Base Font Size</th>
						<th>Use Case</th>
					</tr>
				</thead>
				<tbody>
					<tr>
						<td>sm</td>
						<td>0.875rem</td>
						<td>Sidebars, captions, compact areas</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td>base</td>
						<td>1rem</td>
						<td>Standard content, default option</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td>lg</td>
						<td>1.125rem</td>
						<td>Featured articles, main content</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td>xl</td>
						<td>1.25rem</td>
						<td>Hero sections, landing pages</td>
					</tr>
				</tbody>
			</table>

			<h2>Images and Media</h2>

			<p>
				Images within prose content are automatically styled with proper spacing
				and responsive behavior:
			</p>

			<figure>
				<img
					src="https://via.placeholder.com/600x300/4f46e5/ffffff?text=Typography+Example"
					alt="Example of typography in action"
					width="600"
					height="300"
				/>
				<figcaption>
					Example typography layout showing proper hierarchy and spacing
				</figcaption>
			</figure>

			<hr />

			<h2>Final Notes</h2>

			<p>
				This prose recipe is inspired by <strong>Tailwind Typography</strong>but
				built specifically for our Panda CSS design system. It provides:
			</p>

			<ul>
				<li>Type-safe variant selection</li>
				<li>Design token integration</li>
				<li>Optimal performance with atomic CSS</li>
				<li>Seamless integration with our component library</li>
			</ul>

			<p>
				<em>
					The prose recipe makes it easy to create beautiful, readable content
					without worrying about individual element styling.
				</em>
			</p>
		</Prose>
	</main>
</Layout>
